headline_main: Boris Johnson, China, David Stern: Your Friday Briefing

abstract: As urban areas embrace alternatives to incarceration, the addiction crisis in rural American communities and a different approach to criminal justice have overwhelmed small-town jails.
snippet: As urban areas embrace alternatives to incarceration, the addiction crisis in rural American communities and a different approach to criminal justice have overwhelmed small-town jails.
lead_paragraph: MORRISTOWN, Tenn. — The Hamblen County Jail has been described as a dangerously overcrowded “cesspool of a dungeon,” with inmates sleeping on mats in the hallways, lawyers forced to meet their clients in a supply closet and the people inside subjected to “horrible conditions” every day.

headline_main: ‘A Cesspool of a Dungeon’: The Surging Population in Rural Jails
headline_print_headline: Drug Crisis Ravages Rural America and Fills Its Jails
byline_original: By Richard A. Oppel Jr. and Kristine Potter

abstract: ‘Trump anxiety disorder’ has morphed into anxiety about everything, and impeachment isn’t helping.
snippet: ‘Trump anxiety disorder’ has morphed into anxiety about everything, and impeachment isn’t helping.
lead_paragraph: GREENWOOD, S.C. — The past three years have not been easy for the political fortunes or the emotional health of America’s Democrats. To the extent they feel optimistic about anything, they have been waiting for the 2020 election in the way inhabitants of a storm-ravaged city might look toward the end of hurricane season — as an opportunity to restore order not just to their fractured physical world, but to their battered psyches.

headline_print_headline: As Impeachment and 2020 Loom, Democrats Unite in Worry

abstract: Liu Jingyao, a college student, describes what it’s like to be slut-shamed by 800 million people.
snippet: Liu Jingyao, a college student, describes what it’s like to be slut-shamed by 800 million people.
lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — When Liu Jingyao introduced herself, in the lobby of her apartment building, I didn’t recognize her. It was a puzzling feeling. For an entire year, photos of her had blanketed the Chinese internet. Like tens of millions of other Chinese, I had watched and rewatched surveillance video of her in this very building. She was one of the most talked about and mysterious women in China, and I thought I knew what she looked like.

abstract: Island nations and poor coastal countries facing the severest effects of climate change offer a "moral call to the rest of the world" to act now, former U.S. President Barack Obama said on Friday.
snippet: Island nations and poor coastal countries facing the severest effects of climate change offer a "moral call to the rest of the world" to act now, former U.S. President Barack Obama said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — Island nations and poor coastal countries facing the severest effects of climate change offer a "moral call to the rest of the world" to act now, former U.S. President Barack Obama said on Friday.
headline_main: 'Moral Call to Rest of the World' on Climate From Hardest Hit Countries, Obama Says
headline_print_headline: 'Moral Call to Rest of the World' on Climate From Hardest Hit Countries, Obama Says

abstract: U.S. asylum seekers sent to Guatemala under a new Trump administration program have mostly preferred to return to their country of origin instead of staying in the Central American nation, Guatemala's Interior Minister said on Thursday.
snippet: U.S. asylum seekers sent to Guatemala under a new Trump administration program have mostly preferred to return to their country of origin instead of staying in the Central American nation, Guatemala's Interior Minister said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: GUATEMALA CITY — U.S. asylum seekers sent to Guatemala under a new Trump administration program have mostly preferred to return to their country of origin instead of staying in the Central American nation, Guatemala's Interior Minister said on Thursday.
headline_main: U.S. Asylum Seekers Sent to Guatemala Preferring to Return to Home Countries
headline_print_headline: U.S. Asylum Seekers Sent to Guatemala Preferring to Return to Home Countries

abstract: South Korea has withdrawn from the bidding to host the 2023 Women's World Cup.
snippet: South Korea has withdrawn from the bidding to host the 2023 Women's World Cup.
lead_paragraph: SEOUL, South Korea — South Korea has withdrawn from the bidding to host the 2023 Women's World Cup.
headline_main: South Korea Withdraws Bid for 2023 Women's World Cup
headline_print_headline: South Korea Withdraws Bid for 2023 Women's World Cup

abstract: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party secured a majority in a landslide election victory, results showed on Friday.
snippet: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party secured a majority in a landslide election victory, results showed on Friday.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — British Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party secured a majority in a landslide election victory, results showed on Friday.
headline_main: World Leaders React to Boris Johnson's British Election Victory
headline_print_headline: World Leaders React to Boris Johnson's British Election Victory

abstract: The U.S. special envoy for North Korea will arrive in South Korea on Sunday ahead of a year-end deadline set by Pyongyang for Washington to soften its approach to stalled denucleazisation talks, Seoul and Washington said on Friday.
snippet: The U.S. special envoy for North Korea will arrive in South Korea on Sunday ahead of a year-end deadline set by Pyongyang for Washington to soften its approach to stalled denucleazisation talks, Seoul and Washington said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: SEOUL — The U.S. special envoy for North Korea will arrive in South Korea on Sunday ahead of a year-end deadline set by Pyongyang for Washington to soften its approach to stalled denucleazisation talks, Seoul and Washington said on Friday.
headline_main: U.S. Envoy to Visit Seoul as Deadline Looms for Stalled North Korea Talks
headline_print_headline: U.S. Envoy to Visit Seoul as Deadline Looms for Stalled North Korea Talks
